{
  "texts": [
    "A Gaussian distribution is used to generate the vector at random.",
    "After training, this multidimensional vector space's points will match those in the issue domain, resulting in a compressed representation of the data distribution.",
    "A vector space made up of latent variables is what is referred to as a latent space.",
    "In the case of GANs, the generator assigns meaning to points in a predetermined latent space.",
    "Points selected from the latent space can be given to the generator model as input and used to produce new and distinctive output examples."
  ]
}